A client to Ursa's Taivaanvahti observation database for Jolla's SailfishOS

Description in Jolla Store (ie. the sales pitch)
=================================================

FI: Taivaanvahti on Ursan havaintojärjestelmä, jonka tietokantaan kerätään 
tähtitieteellisten ja ilmakehän ilmiöiden havaintoja. Tällä 
sovelluksella voit selata Taivaanvahtiin syötettyjä havaintoja ja pysyt 
kartalla siitä mitä avaruudessa ja Suomen taivaalla tapahtuu.

EN: Taivaanvahti is a sky observation database maintained by Ursa. With this 
application you can browse the observations in Taivaanvahti's database 
and keep up-to-date with heavenly happenings in deep space and around 
Finland.

NOTE: English translation maybe be included later in future
NOTE: Most of the observations are in Finnish

Build
======

Load the project in QtCreator (SailfishOS version used, others might 
work) and build it there.

The usual qmake routine of

 qmake && make && make install
 
should also work.

Install
========

Prefer to install the tested relases from Jolla Store.

To build a package your self, use the mb or mb2 tools within a SailfishOS
or Mer SDK. Details of that are left as an exercise for now.

Once you have a package, just get it on the device through ssh / bluetooth
and run

 pkcon install-local harbour-taivaanvahti*.rpm

You might need to be in developer mode for that to work.

